# 9. Why This Works

Every substring of `word` is generated exactly once.

If a pattern exists,

```
pattern ∈ substrings
```

Otherwise,

```
pattern ∉ substrings
```

Hash set lookup is O(1) average.

Therefore every pattern is checked efficiently.

